      en: {
        metaTitle: "Taxi Toulouse → Lourdes | Fixed price from €240 | TaxiNeo",
        metaDescription: "Taxi Toulouse → Lourdes. 190 km, 2h, fixed price from €240. Sanctuary, pilgrimage, wheelchair accessible. Book 24/7.",
        heroTitle: "Taxi Toulouse → Lourdes",
        heroSubtitle: "Your Toulouse → Lourdes transfer at €240 — €300. 190 km via the A64 to the Pyrenees.",
        description: "Lourdes, a world pilgrimage destination with 6 million visitors a year, is 2h from Toulouse via the A64.",
        routeDescription: "The route follows the A64 towards Bayonne, crossing the Pyrenean foothills via Saint-Gaudens and Tarbes, exit Lourdes.",
        introduction: "Lourdes is the world's second-largest Catholic pilgrimage site after the Vatican, with over 6 million visitors annually. Since the apparitions of the Virgin Mary to Bernadette Soubirous in 1858, the Notre-Dame de Lourdes sanctuaries have welcomed pilgrims from around the world, including many sick or disabled people hoping for miraculous healing. The Grotto domain, with the Basilica of the Immaculate Conception, the Rosary Basilica, the underground Basilica of Saint Pius X (seating 25,000), and the miraculous baths, forms a religious complex of extraordinary scale. Lourdes is also a gateway to the Pyrenees: the Pic du Midi de Bigorre (2,877 m, observatory with exceptional panorama), the Cirque de Gavarnie (UNESCO), and the spa towns of Cauterets and Barèges. A taxi from Toulouse is particularly suited to disabled pilgrims (our vehicles are wheelchair-accessible on request), family groups and elderly visitors who cannot comfortably take the train with their luggage and medical equipment.",
        itineraire: "From Toulouse, your driver takes the A64 (La Pyrénéenne) towards Bayonne. The motorway follows the Pyrenean foothills with an ever-growing view of the Pyrenees chain as you travel further from Toulouse. You pass Saint-Gaudens, a sub-prefecture at the foot of the central Pyrenees, then Lannemezan (junction for the Pyrenean valleys). At Tarbes, you leave the A64 for the Lourdes road via the D921. The landscape changes dramatically: green foothills give way to the first mountains, and the Pic du Midi de Bigorre appears to the south with its observatory. Arrival in Lourdes is via Boulevard de la Grotte, the main artery leading directly to the sanctuaries. Total tolls are approximately €16. The journey takes 2h normally and can reach 2h30 during major pilgrimages (Assumption on 15 August, All Saints') when the road between Tarbes and Lourdes is saturated.",
        conseils: "The busiest periods in Lourdes are the week around 15 August (Assumption) and national pilgrimages (May to October). During these periods, book your taxi at least a week in advance. For wheelchair pilgrims, specify this when booking: we have adapted vehicles and our drivers can help with equipment. The Grotto domain is fully wheelchair-accessible. If you wish to visit the Pic du Midi de Bigorre (1h30 drive from Lourdes + cable car), book a full day with hourly hire. For accommodation, Lourdes hotels are often full during pilgrimages — many pilgrims stay in Tarbes (20 min) and use taxi transfers. The torchlight procession (9pm, every evening April to October) is an unforgettable experience.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TGV Toulouse — Lourdes costs €25-50 and takes 1h50. It is a fast option for independent travellers, but Lourdes station is 1.5 km from the sanctuaries — a distance that can be challenging for those with reduced mobility. The Lio bus costs €2 but takes 3h30. By car, expect €25 in fuel and €16 in tolls. The TaxiNeo taxi at €240 — €300 is the preferred solution for sick or disabled pilgrims: home or airport pick-up, drop-off at the sanctuary entrance, help with luggage and medical equipment. For 4 passengers, the cost (€60-75 per person) is comparable to the train for incomparably superior service.",
        faq: [
          { question: "Can the taxi carry a wheelchair?", answer: "Yes, our sedans accommodate a folding wheelchair in the boot. For an electric wheelchair, choose our Van service. Specify your accessibility needs when booking." },
          { question: "Where does the taxi drop me in Lourdes?", answer: "Directly at the Notre-Dame de Lourdes sanctuary entrance (Boulevard de la Grotte) or at your hotel address. Our drivers know the authorised drop-off zones even during pilgrimage periods." },
          { question: "Can I go to the Pic du Midi from Lourdes by taxi?", answer: "Yes, the Pic du Midi is accessible via La Mongie (1h30 drive). The taxi drops you at the cable car departure. Plan a full day with hourly hire." },
          { question: "How much are the Toulouse — Lourdes tolls?", answer: "A64 tolls total approximately €16, included in the TaxiNeo fixed price." },
          { question: "Is a taxi available for the return after the evening procession?", answer: "Yes, we provide Lourdes → Toulouse evening returns (after 9pm, torchlight procession). Book the return at the same time as the outward journey." }
        ],
      },
